rom 2016, the actor attaching a photo of himself and Obama in 2013 as a “Throwback Thursday” pic. “Thanks for your service and for your advice,” Boseman told Obama at the time, going on to refer to himself and the former leader as “the prince and the president.” NY Post Vanguard Chadwick Boseman, the star of the ground-breaking superhero movie "Black Panther," has died from colon cancer, his publicist told AFP Friday. Boseman, who was in his 40s, had not publicly discussed his condition -- which was first diagnosed in 2016 -- and continued to work on major Hollywood films. "It… August 29, 2020 In "Entertainment" Superhero movie “Black Panther’ made a killing at the MTV Movie & TV Awards winning four trophies. June 19, 2018 In "Showtime People" Former US president Barack Obama on Wednesday applauded the "profound" protests by Americans demanding racial justice and said demonstrations over last week's killing of a black man in police custody could spark nationwide reforms. In his first video comments since George Floyd's death on May 25 in Minneapolis triggered unrest… June 4, 2020 In "Foreign"